===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

{{liushu|psc}}: Formed by adding a handle to {{och-l|同|tr=*lˤoŋ}}, which also acts as the phonetic component.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*z(j)um ~ *zuŋ}}, provisionally set up by [https://stedt.berkeley.edu STEDT]. Cognates to {{och-l|傭|tr=loŋ}} and {{och-l|庸|tr=loŋ}}, outside Sinitic, {{cog|bfs|zv³¹||to use}} {{cog|my|သုံး||to use}}, {{cog|ers|zi⁵⁵||to use}}, {{cog|ii|ꌬ||to use}}, {{cog|blk|tr=sūŋ|t=to use}}.

{{zh-ref|Sun (1999)}} and {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} consider this word a cognate to {{cog|bo|ལོངས||use}}

'''Definition 10''' comes sound-matching of the character [[蓉]] from the term [[細蓉]] / [[细蓉]].

